subproject.corporate outcome:
- Civic engagement, through civil society organizations, voluntary associations, trade unions, political parties, and private sector organizations, enables all people to influence public policy processes. 
- Electoral laws, processes and institutions strengthen inclusive participation and professional electoral administration 
- Communication channels support government accountability and transparency through e-governance, independent journalism, and access to information policies
subproject.description: The project aims to support disadvantaged women and their families through providing them with economic and social services, psychosocial support, recreational  and awareness raising interventions. The project is considered high priority for Gazan women and their families.The project contributes to empower women in Gaza through enhancing women’s skills in organizing, addressing their own problems and increasing income. The outcome of the project is the improvement of access to social and economic services for women and their families in Nuseirat and Jabalia. It will be achieved through the training of women in Jabalia and Nuseirat in providing sustainable social and economic services.
subproject.gender code: Gender equality as a significant objective
subproject.title: Community-Based Women Empowerm
